# Lab Setup Guide (Linux) – Docker, Minikube, Terraform, Git, Kubernetes

## Objective
This guide installs all required tools on a fresh Linux system to run Docker, Kubernetes (Minikube), Terraform, Git, and related lab tasks.

---

## STEP 1: Update System

sudo apt update
sudo apt upgrade -y

---

## STEP 2: Install Git

sudo apt install -y git

# verify
git --version

---

## STEP 3: Install Docker

sudo apt install -y docker.io

# start docker
sudo systemctl start docker
sudo systemctl enable docker

# add user to docker group (avoid sudo)
sudo usermod -aG docker $USER

# apply changes
newgrp docker

# verify
docker --version

---

## STEP 4: Install kubectl (Kubernetes CLI)

sudo apt install -y kubectl

# verify
kubectl version --client

---

## STEP 5: Install Minikube

curl -LO https://storage.googleapis.com/minikube/releases/latest/minikube-linux-amd64

sudo install minikube-linux-amd64 /usr/local/bin/minikube

# verify
minikube version

---

## STEP 6: Start Minikube

minikube start --driver=docker

# verify
minikube status
kubectl cluster-info

---

## STEP 7: Use Minikube Docker

eval $(minikube docker-env)

---

## STEP 8: Install Terraform

sudo apt install -y wget unzip

wget https://releases.hashicorp.com/terraform/1.5.0/terraform_1.5.0_linux_amd64.zip

unzip terraform_1.5.0_linux_amd64.zip

sudo mv terraform /usr/local/bin/

# verify
terraform -version

---

## STEP 9: Install Helm (for Prometheus)

curl https://raw.githubusercontent.com/helm/helm/main/scripts/get-helm-3 | bash

# verify
helm version

---

## STEP 10: Install OpenFaaS CLI (arkade)

curl -sLS https://get.arkade.dev | sudo sh

# verify
arkade version

---

## STEP 11: Install faas-cli

curl -sSL https://cli.openfaas.com | sudo sh

# verify
faas-cli version

---

## STEP 12: Install MongoDB

sudo apt install -y mongodb

# start mongodb
sudo systemctl start mongodb

# open shell
mongosh

---

## STEP 13: Clone Lab Repository

git clone https://github.com/Raghavsharma10/cicd.git

cd cicd

---

## STEP 14: Navigate to Any Lab

cd l5-minikube
ls
cat flow.md

---

## IMPORTANT NOTES

- Always run: eval $(minikube docker-env)
- Keep terminal open when using: minikube service
- Ports change every run (check output)
- Use: kubectl get pods (to debug)
- Use: docker images (to verify builds)

---

## QUICK CHECK

docker --version
kubectl version --client
minikube version
terraform -version
git --version

---

## CONCLUSION

All required tools are installed and system is ready to run Docker, Kubernetes, Terraform, OpenFaaS, and CI/CD labs.

